<article data-view="I4" contenteditable="true" tabindex="1"><h1>Signals</h1><div>When a controller processes a signal through an <span style="font-style: italic;">action</span>, the following<br></div><div>properties are set:</div><div><ul><li><span style="font-weight: bold;">on</span>: the current object receiving the signal.</li><li><span style="font-weight: bold;">action</span>: the current action.&nbsp; If the action is changed, the controller will process that action if it is defined on the controller.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li></ul><span style="font-family: sans-serif;"><div><span style="font-family: sans-serif;"><br></span></div>If the action&nbsp;</span><br><span style="font-family: sans-serif; font-weight: bold;">content</span><span style="font-family: sans-serif;">: the content of the signal.&nbsp; This can be any value.</span><br><span style="font-family: sans-serif;"><div><br></div><div>A signal also also has a Symbol.Signal with a value of:<br></div></span></div><div><ul><li><span style="font-family: sans-serif;">Message: "down"</span></li><li><span style="font-family: sans-serif;">Event: "up"</span></li><li><span style="font-family: sans-serif;">Broadcast</span></li></ul><span style="font-family: sans-serif;">The Symbol.Signal isn't fully developed yet.</span></div><div><span style="font-family: sans-serif;"><br></span></div><div><span style="font-family: sans-serif;"><br></span></div><div><span style="font-family: sans-serif;"><br></span></div></article>